---
/**
 * src/pages/about.astro — About Haynes Industrial Medicine
 */

import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Haynes Industrial Medicine"
  description="Haynes Industrial Medicine provides DOT drug testing, respirator fit testing, and CPR/AED training for industrial workforces. Learn about our background and approach."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-brand-900 dark:text-white">About Us</h1>

    <div class="prose-content mt-8">
      <p>
        Haynes Industrial Medicine exists because we've seen what happens when
        compliance testing and safety training are treated as an afterthought —
        or when a clinic that doesn't understand industrial work is handling your
        workforce's requirements.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Industrial background section -->
    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-8 sm:flex-row sm:items-start">
      <div class="shrink-0 sm:w-56">
        <img
          src="/images/about/jon-field.gif"
          alt="Jon Haynes working in the field at an industrial site"
          class="w-full rounded-lg object-cover shadow-md"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="prose-content">
        <h2 class="mt-0">Fifteen Years in Industrial Operations</h2>
        <p>
          The Haynes family has spent over fifteen years running industrial
          operations — managing crews, navigating OSHA audits, and dealing with
          the real pressure of keeping a workforce productive and compliant at
          the same time. We know what it's like when a testing clinic sends
          results in the wrong format, or a trainer doesn't show up when your
          crew is already assembled and waiting.
        </p>
        <p>
          That operational background isn't a side note — it's why we exist.
          We built this practice specifically to serve employers like the ones
          we used to be.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Medical background section -->
    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-8 sm:flex-row-reverse sm:items-start">
      <div class="shrink-0 sm:w-56">
        <img
          src="/images/about/jon-doc.jpeg"
          alt="Jon Haynes as an emergency medicine physician"
          class="w-full rounded-lg object-cover shadow-md"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="prose-content">
        <h2 class="mt-0">Emergency Medicine Training</h2>
        <p>
          Jon Haynes is also a trained emergency medicine physician. That clinical
          background means the medical side of this practice isn't outsourced or
          delegated to whoever's available — it's grounded in real emergency
          medicine experience and a deep understanding of how the body responds
          to occupational exposures and acute injury.
        </p>
        <p>
          The combination is unusual: an operator who's run crews and a physician
          who's treated the workers those crews send to the ER. That perspective
          shapes everything from how we conduct fit testing to how we train your
          team on CPR and AED response.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-content mt-10">
      <h2>What We're Focused On</h2>
      <p>
        We're building this practice around three services industrial employers
        need regularly and need done right:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>DOT Drug Testing</strong> — DOT-compliant urine drug screens
          for regulated employers. Pre-employment, random, post-accident, and
          reasonable suspicion. MRO review included.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Respirator Fit Testing</strong> — OSHA-required quantitative
          and qualitative fit testing for tight-fitting respirators, with proper
          documentation for your records.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>CPR/AED Training</strong> — Certification courses for
          individuals and work groups, scheduled around your operation and
          conducted at your facility when that's easier.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Work</h2>
      <p>
        We keep things simple. Same-day drug testing is almost always available.
        Fit testing and CPR/AED training can be scheduled around your shifts — and
        we'll come to your facility when that works better. Documentation goes
        directly to your safety team, ready for your files.
      </p>
      <p>
        We're not a volume clinic. We're a small operation that takes the time to
        understand your compliance program and your schedule.
      </p>

      <h2>Get In Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Ready to set up testing or schedule a training? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a>
        or give us a call. We'll figure out what you need and get it done.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
